This paper deals with the problem of secure communication over a wiretap channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of multiple receivers and eavesdroppers makes it relevant to the sub-categories of multiple access channels (cs.MM) and network information theory (cs.NI). The study of the Gaussian MIMO channel model also makes it relevant to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
